(796, 1, '2009-06-04 03:06:50', '2009-06-04 10:06:50', '<a href="http://www.happyphoton.com/2009/06/04/interview-robert-3-rsj-johnson/"><img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/e1a5_2897666996_b6bfd954d2.jpg" alt="" /></a>\r\n\r\nI am 25, I have a degree in philosophy.\r\n\r\nI have always been creating, either drawings or music, arranging objects, concepts, photography came natural. I have always ''been into it''. I inherited my fathers 35 mm Nikon, which I have since destroyed.\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<strong>What is your most proud photo?</strong>\r\n\r\nI am most proud of the photos i took during a series of\r\nprotests/riots in Seoul, Korea. I was injured during the\r\ncourse of that protest, which i am very pleased/proud of.\r\n\r\n<strong>How do you relax?</strong>\r\n\r\nI am always relaxed. But I become most stressed playing go.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is the most challenging for you in photography?</strong>\r\n\r\nI am trying to understand photography. What is a photograph? A captured moment? Artistic creation? Documentation, narration? Photography places itself in a middle space. Understanding where to locate photography is very difficult for me.\r\n\r\n<strong>When did you cry last time?</strong>\r\n\r\nEvery morning I hold back my tears.\r\n<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/9570918@N02/"> 3-rsj on flickr</a>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/0053_2549862843_8e95ca79f0.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/b7a1_2452789329_4cbdc80f2e.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/cd2d_2452789651_6b62c9ab14.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/3d63_3342031166_2453e49c32.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/8daf_3312460725_e641b0b770.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/0927