(820, 1, '2009-06-05 09:01:31', '2009-06-05 16:01:31', '<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/e2fa_2862715264_40782309b7.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\nI am currently in Ube, Japan, which is rural, industrial, and on the southern tip of the main island. I am headed back home to the United States in three weeks. I am not a professional photographer, but pinning it as a hobby seems somehow incorrect. Listening to records is certainly a hobby though.\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<strong>What equipment do you use?</strong>\r\n\r\nI have two Contax 35mm cameras (T2 and G1) and an old Rolleiflex. I usually shoot with Kodak Portra.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is the source of your inspiration?</strong>\r\n\r\nI am not sure if I could nail down one source of inspiration. All of my friends take better pictures than I do, and that keeps me inspired in a strange way.  Also just looking at tons of pictures and learning about the mechanics of photography always gets me looking at things differently.\r\n\r\n<strong>Where is your favorite place in the world?</strong>\r\n\r\nHonestly, maybe Tennessee.\r\n\r\n<strong> What book changed your life?</strong>\r\n\r\nGravity’s Rainbow\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/benacree/">Ben Acree on flickr</a>\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/92e0_3235147277_93df3e3453.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/498b_3176238977_ff63b189ab.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/47eb_2915318938_85c3c1de13.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/a8c4_2862689954_b80f636578.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/ea91_3464185980_9506b9d90f.jpg" alt="" />', 'Interview: Ben Acree', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'interview-ben-acree', '', '', '2009-09-23 15:33:51', '2009-09-23 22:33:51', '', 0, 'http://www.happyphoton.com/?p=