(871, 1, '2009-06-05 09:18:55', '2009-06-05 16:18:55', '<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/e2fa_2862715264_40782309b7.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\nI am currently in Ube, Japan, which is rural, industrial, and on the southern tip of the main island. I am headed back home to the United States in three weeks. I am not a professional photographer, but pinning it as a hobby seems somehow incorrect. Listening to records is certainly a hobby though.\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<strong>What equipment do you use?</strong>\r\n\r\nI have two Contax 35mm cameras (T2 and G1) and an old Rolleiflex. I usually shoot with Kodak Portra.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is the source of your inspiration?</strong>\r\n\r\nI am not sure if I could nail down one source of inspiration. All of my friends take better pictures than I do, and that keeps me inspired in a strange way.  Also just looking at tons of pictures and learning about the mechanics of photography always gets me looking at things differently.\r\n\r\n<strong>Where is your favorite place in the world?</strong>\r\n\r\nHonestly, maybe Tennessee.\r\n\r\n<strong> What book changed your life?</strong>\r\n\r\nGravity’s Rainbow\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/benacree/">Ben Acree on flickr</a>\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/92e0_3235147277_93df3e3453.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/498b_3176238977_ff63b189ab.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/47eb_2915318938_85c3c1de13.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/a8c4_2862689954_b80f636578.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/ea91_3464185980_9506b9d90f.jpg" alt="" />', 'Interview: Ben Acree', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '820-revision-3', '', '', '2009-06-05 09:18:55', '2009-06-05 16:18:55', '', 820, 'http://www.happyphoton.com/2009/06/05/820-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(872, 1, '2009-09-02 08:17:26', '2009-09-02 15:17:26', '<a href="http://www.happyphoton.com/2009/06/04/interview-robert-3-rsj-johnson/"><img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/e1a5_2897666996_b6bfd954d2.jpg" alt="" /></a>\r\n\r\nI am 25, I have a degree in philosophy.\r\n\r\nI have always been creating, either drawings or music, arranging objects, concepts, photography came natural. I have always ''been into it''. I inherited my fathers 35 mm Nikon, which I have since destroyed.\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<strong>What is your most proud photo?</strong>\r\n\r\nI am most proud of the photos i took during a series of\r\nprotests/riots in Seoul, Korea. I was injured during the\r\ncourse of that protest, which i am very pleased/proud of.\r\n\r\n<strong>How do you relax?</strong>\r\n\r\nI am always relaxed. But I become most stressed playing go.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is the most challenging for you in photography?</strong>\r\n\r\nI am trying to understand photography. What is a photograph? A captured moment? Artistic creation? Documentation, narration? Photography places itself in a middle space. Understanding where to locate photography is very difficult for me.\r\n\r\n<strong>When did you cry last time?</strong>\r\n\r\nEvery morning I hold back my tears.\r\n<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/9570918@N02/"> 3-rsj on flickr</a>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/0053_2549862843_8e95ca79f0.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/b7a1_2452789329_4cbdc80f2e.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/cd2d_2452789651_6b62c9ab14.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/3d63_3342031166_2453e49c32.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/8daf_3312460725_e641b0b770.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/0927_3505758550_96ede2a09f.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/77b2_3313285368_772fb46e4c.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/0609_2279311782_2479574347.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/0ea9_3505758498_1f5b05affb.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/f585_2983420596_d31962f321.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/5999_3426500155_90d7820f45.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/4b91_2948802998_89e323ea77.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/7f1e_2150394464_853dd60a6f.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/7bc7_3584728755_8a413d0080.jpg" alt="" />', 'Interview: Robert ''3-rsj'' Johnson', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '796-revision-6', '', '', '2009-09-02 08:17:26', '2009-09-02 15:17:26', '', 796, 'http://www.happyphoton.com/2009/09/02/796-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
