(953, 1, '2008-09-04 15:00:29', '2008-09-04 22:00:29', '<a href="http://www.happyphoton.com/2008/09/04/alberta-ferretti-fall-2008-campaign-by-steven-meisel/"><img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/2/01.jpg" alt="" /></a>\r\n\r\nSteven Meisel (born 1954) is an American photographer, who obtained popular acclaim with his work in US and Italian Vogue and his photographs of friend Madonna in the latter''s 1992 book Sex designed by Fabien Baron.\r\n\r\n<strong>The location is great, isn''t it?</strong>\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/2/02.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/2/03.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/2/04.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/2/05.jpg" alt="" />', 'Alberta Ferretti Fall 2008 campaign by Steven Meisel', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '9-revision-4', '', '', '2008-09-04 15:00:29', '2008-09-04 22:00:29', '', 9, 'http://www.happyphoton.com/2008/09/04/9-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(954, 1, '2008-09-07 13:43:54', '2008-09-07 20:43:54', '<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/01.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>John Scarisbrick</strong> is one of Sweden’s most established and celebrated international fashion photographers. After six succesful years in New York in the nineties, he re-located to his hometown Stockholm in 2001. During his New York career, John was known for a highly distinctive and personal style of photography, full of energy and with interesting, often radical angles, largely influenced by punk music and other sub-cultural phenomena. In later years, his style has become more mature, subtle and sophisticated, more close and intimate with his models, oriented to beauty as well as fashion. John is also a great portrait photographer with an impressive portfolio full\r\nof actors, artists, atheletes, musicians and a host of other celebrities. \r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/02.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/03.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/04.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/05.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/06.jpg" alt="" />', 'Diesel fall/winter compaign by John Scarisbrick', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-revision-3', '', '', '2008-09-07 13:43:54', '2008-09-07 20:43:54', '', 7, 'http://www.happyphoton.com/2008/09/07/7-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(955, 1, '2008-09-04 14:02:05', '2008-09-04 21:02:05', '<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/2.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\nRebekka Ehlers was born in Aarhus, Denmark in 1977.\r\nThe majority of her education was obtained at the Danish Art School of Photography, but it also consisted of studies and work periods in London, Copenhagen, and Catena di Villorba. In 2003 she received a scholarship from Fabrica, the benetton research and communications center, where she worked until starting out as a freelance photographer in 2005.\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/3.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/4.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.happyphoton.com/images/2008/08/04/5.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\nsee more at <a href="http://www.rebekkaehlers.com/">rebekkaehlers.com</a>', 'Rebekka Ehlers for Reef N'' Beef Australian restaurant', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-2', '', '', '2008-09-04 14:02:05', '2008-09-04 21:02:05', '', 5, 'http://www.happyphoton.com/2008/09/04/5-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
